choices.text:
choosing what to eat. There’s so many different things and so many different places! But it is definitely worth it :). When we were in the US, the only good food we had were the views in Hawaii (coolest places ever :D). That sort of food (especially for breakfast) was something I remember best from USA, but also the best mint tea/lavender and lavender ice cream (oh, so good) from France. Healthy things – nope, no one in Macedonia drinks green tea and not many people have heard of acai berries or any exotic ingredients. Fruit salads are very popular though, we do eat a lot of fruit. I’ve only had waffles one time in the US, they are popular in Macedonia, we eat them a lot, they’re my favorites because they fill you up but don’t have too many calories. But the crêpes! I’ve fallen in love with crêpes! They’re small, delicious and if you fill them with something healthy, they’re basically perfect :)! So we Europeans have low tolerance for strange and exotic food you guys eat ;)

Btw, I hope I’ll do well in my exams, but thanks for wishing me luck :)

LOOL. aree you in Montenegro, Jordan, Algeria or Morocco?

The perspective on American food is so much more flattering here, we Europeans have to eat, meat and diet products first, but you guys eat fruit with every meal, and vegetables are the basis!
